main event: Five bright, round objects were observed in the sky, alternating between orange-red and white colors.
interesting points: The objects moved up and down and sideways.
The objects gradually faded over the course of the 15-minute observation period.
The sighting occurred on November 10, 1957, from 2311 to 0005Z.
The conclusion listed on the Project 10073 Record Card was 'Other'.
